    {
      "id": "ac0fcdef6550b6915eda02d8fc3a29d2e82693a8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2015-07-22 15:59:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nGregoire - From the MDS console it looks like the LBUG in tgt_request_handle() is getting exercised. Logs are at: https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/7cdfa17a-3075-11e5-9b7c-5254006e85c2",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "2f2847af16bc0ba71f94a273c2b7205311988679",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2015-07-22 18:53:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.6/x86_64: (https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/c7487cdc-30a2-11e5-9b7c-5254006e85c2).  Ran 13 tests.  2 tests failed: sanity-hsm, sanity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "7878d9b7a22ba7fb32e696f857b24792a198453b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 163,
        "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
        "email": "gregoire.pichon@eviden.com",
        "username": "pichong"
      },
      "date": "2015-07-23 15:22:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHere is what happened during test_17m.\n\n1. the MDT target is in recovery\n2. the target received a MDS_CONNECT RPC that sets the export last xid to value A\n3. the target received a LDLM_ENQUEUE RPC with an xid lower than export last xid value A\n4. this triggers LBUG\n\nHow is it possible that the client sends the LDLM_ENQUEUE RPC (without RESEND and REPLAY flag) after the MDS_CONNECT RPC and that the MDS_CONNECT RPC was not aware of the LDLM_ENQUEUE RPC when it computed its last_xid ?\n\nNeed to check if the strategy implemented in patch http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/15473/ better handle this situation.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "eaf5c9320b479950c0ad413fac6539d07e599a82",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-07-23 16:13:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nreq@ffff8800583e4cc0 x1507391906516184/t0(4294967471) o101->b38f7cba-d40e-8893-fb0d-b132d362ed5c@10.1.4.94@tcp:505/0 lens 872/0 e 0 to 0 dl 1437561275 ref 1 fl Interpret:/4/ffffffff rc 0/-1\n\nThat looks like a REPLAY request to me, so it may carry a smaller last_xid. (than the connect request), but it won't hurt anybody, because client can only start replay on connect reply received.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0109c0edd870795ac666489ca9dd34f43af1015b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 163,
        "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
        "email": "gregoire.pichon@eviden.com",
        "username": "pichong"
      },
      "date": "2015-07-24 07:59:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe request does not have the REPLAY flag:\n\"fl Interpret:/4/ffffffff\"",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "e62c236081b4619cdc27ea3033ca90e865b1a6b3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-07-24 09:08:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIsn't '4' the MSG_REPLAY?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "260793758b881e9d1d91ae956222195aedfd9bab",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 163,
        "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
        "email": "gregoire.pichon@eviden.com",
        "username": "pichong"
      },
      "date": "2015-07-24 10:31:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nMy mistake. This is a REPLAY request.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
